  53. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_quick_stat(value v)
  54. {
  55.   CAMLparam0 ();
  56.   CAMLlocal1 (res);

  58.   /* get a copy of these before allocating anything... */
  59.   intnat majcoll, mincoll;
  60.   struct gc_stats s;
  61.   caml_compute_gc_stats(&s);
  62.   majcoll = caml_major_cycles_completed;
  63.   mincoll = atomic_load(&caml_minor_collections_count);

  65.   res = caml_alloc_tuple (17);
  66.   Store_field (res, 0, caml_copy_double ((double)s.alloc_stats.minor_words));
  67.   Store_field (res, 1, caml_copy_double ((double)s.alloc_stats.promoted_words));
  68.   Store_field (res, 2, caml_copy_double ((double)s.alloc_stats.major_words));
  69.   Store_field (res, 3, Val_long (mincoll));
  70.   Store_field (res, 4, Val_long (majcoll));
  71.   Store_field (res, 5, Val_long (
  72.     s.heap_stats.pool_words + s.heap_stats.large_words));
  73.   Store_field (res, 6, Val_long (0));
  74.   Store_field (res, 7, Val_long (
  75.     s.heap_stats.pool_live_words + s.heap_stats.large_words));
  76.   Store_field (res, 8, Val_long (
  77.     s.heap_stats.pool_live_blocks + s.heap_stats.large_blocks));
  78.   Store_field (res, 9, Val_long (
  79.     s.heap_stats.pool_words - s.heap_stats.pool_live_words
  80.     - s.heap_stats.pool_frag_words));
  81.   Store_field (res, 10, Val_long (0));
  82.   Store_field (res, 11, Val_long (0));
  83.   Store_field (res, 12, Val_long (s.heap_stats.pool_frag_words));
  84.   Store_field (res, 13, Val_long (0));
  85.   Store_field (res, 14, Val_long (
  86.     s.heap_stats.pool_max_words + s.heap_stats.large_max_words));
  87.   Store_field (res, 15, Val_long (0));
  88.   Store_field (res, 16, Val_long (s.alloc_stats.forced_major_collections));
  89.   CAMLreturn (res);
  90. }

  105. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_counters(value v)
  106. {
  107.   CAMLparam0 ();   /* v is ignored */
  108.   CAMLlocal1 (res);

  110.   /* get a copy of these before allocating anything... */
  111.   double minwords = Caml_state->stat_minor_words
  112.     + ((double) Wsize_bsize ((uintnat)Caml_state->young_end -
  113.         (uintnat) Caml_state->young_ptr)) / sizeof(value);
  114.   double prowords = Caml_state->stat_promoted_words;
  115.   double majwords = Caml_state->stat_major_words +
  116.                     (double) Caml_state->allocated_words;

  118.   res = caml_alloc_3(0,
  119.     caml_copy_double (minwords),
  120.     caml_copy_double (prowords),
  121.     caml_copy_double (majwords));
  122.   CAMLreturn (res);
  123. }

  158. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_set(value v)
  159. {
  160.   uintnat newminwsz = caml_norm_minor_heap_size (Long_val (Field (v, 0)));
  161.   uintnat newpf = norm_pfree (Long_val (Field (v, 2)));
  162.   uintnat new_verb_gc = Long_val (Field (v, 3));
  163.   uintnat new_max_stack_size = Long_val (Field (v, 5));
  164.   uintnat new_custom_maj = norm_custom_maj (Long_val (Field (v, 8)));
  165.   uintnat new_custom_min = norm_custom_min (Long_val (Field (v, 9)));
  166.   uintnat new_custom_sz = Long_val (Field (v, 10));

  168.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_SET);

  170.   caml_change_max_stack_size (new_max_stack_size);

  172.   if (newpf != caml_percent_free){
  173.     caml_percent_free = newpf;
  174.     caml_gc_message (0x20, "New space overhead: %"
  175.                      ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "u%%\n", caml_percent_free);
  176.   }

  178.   atomic_store_relaxed(&caml_verb_gc, new_verb_gc);

  180.   /* These fields were added in 4.08.0. */
  181.   if (Wosize_val (v) >= 11){
  182.     if (new_custom_maj != caml_custom_major_ratio){
  183.       caml_custom_major_ratio = new_custom_maj;
  184.       caml_gc_message (0x20, "New custom major ratio: %"
  185.                        ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "u%%\n",
  186.                        caml_custom_major_ratio);
  187.     }
  188.     if (new_custom_min != caml_custom_minor_ratio){
  189.       caml_custom_minor_ratio = new_custom_min;
  190.       caml_gc_message (0x20, "New custom minor ratio: %"
  191.                        ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "u%%\n",
  192.                        caml_custom_minor_ratio);
  193.     }
  194.     if (new_custom_sz != caml_custom_minor_max_bsz){
  195.       caml_custom_minor_max_bsz = new_custom_sz;
  196.       caml_gc_message (0x20, "New custom minor size limit: %"
  197.                        ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "u%%\n",
  198.                        caml_custom_minor_max_bsz);
  199.     }
  200.   }

  202.   /* Minor heap size comes last because it will trigger a minor collection
  203.      (thus invalidating [v]) and it can raise [Out_of_memory]. */
  204.   if (newminwsz != Caml_state->minor_heap_wsz) {
  205.     caml_gc_message (0x20, "New minor heap size: %"
  206.                      ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "uk words\n", newminwsz / 1024);
  207.   }

  209.   if (newminwsz > caml_minor_heap_max_wsz) {
  210.     caml_gc_log ("update minor heap max: %"
  211.                  ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "uk words", newminwsz / 1024);
  212.     caml_update_minor_heap_max(newminwsz);
  213.   }
  214.   CAMLassert(newminwsz <= caml_minor_heap_max_wsz);
  215.   if (newminwsz != Caml_state->minor_heap_wsz) {
  216.     caml_gc_log ("current minor heap size: %"
  217.                  ARCH_SIZET_PRINTF_FORMAT "uk words",
  218.                  Caml_state->minor_heap_wsz / 1024);
  219.     caml_gc_log ("set minor heap size: %"
  220.                  ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "uk words", newminwsz / 1024);
  221.     /* FIXME: when (newminwsz > caml_minor_heap_max_wsz) and
  222.        (newminwsz != Caml_state->minor_heap_wsz) are both true,
  223.        the current domain reallocates its own minor heap twice. */
  224.     caml_set_minor_heap_size (newminwsz);
  225.   }

  227.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_SET);
  228.   return Val_unit;
  229. }

  231. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_minor(value v)
  232. {
  233.   Caml_check_caml_state();
  234.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_MINOR);
  235.   CAMLassert (v == Val_unit);
  236.   caml_minor_collection ();
  237.   value exn = caml_process_pending_actions_exn();
  238.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_MINOR);
  239.   return caml_raise_if_exception(exn);
  240. }

  242. ‌static value gc_major_exn(void)
  243. {
  244.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_MAJOR);
  245.   caml_gc_log ("Major GC cycle requested");
  246.   caml_empty_minor_heaps_once();
  247.   caml_finish_major_cycle();
  248.   value exn = caml_process_pending_actions_exn();
  249.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_MAJOR);
  250.   return exn;
  251. }

  253. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_major(value v)
  254. {
  255.   Caml_check_caml_state();
  256.   CAMLassert (v == Val_unit);
  257.   return caml_raise_if_exception(gc_major_exn());
  258. }

  260. ‌static value gc_full_major_exn(void)
  261. {
  262.   int i;
  263.   value exn = Val_unit;
  264.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_FULL_MAJOR);
  265.   caml_gc_log ("Full Major GC requested");
  266.   /* In general, it can require up to 3 GC cycles for a
  267.      currently-unreachable object to be collected. */
  268.   for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
  269.     caml_empty_minor_heaps_once();
  270.     caml_finish_major_cycle();
  271.     exn = caml_process_pending_actions_exn();
  272.     if (Is_exception_result(exn)) break;
  273.   }
  274.   ++ Caml_state->stat_forced_major_collections;
  275.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_FULL_MAJOR);
  276.   return exn;
  277. }

  279. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_full_major(value v)
  280. {
  281.   Caml_check_caml_state();
  282.   CAMLassert (v == Val_unit);
  283.   return caml_raise_if_exception(gc_full_major_exn());
  284. }

  296. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_compaction(value v)
  297. {
  298.   Caml_check_caml_state();
  299.   value exn = Val_unit;
  300.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_COMPACT);
  301.   CAMLassert (v == Val_unit);
  302.   exn = gc_major_exn();
  303.   ++ Caml_state->stat_forced_major_collections;
  304.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_COMPACT);
  305.   return exn;
  306. }

  308. ‌CAMLprim value caml_gc_stat(value v)
  309. {
  310.   value res;
  311.   CAML_EV_BEGIN(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_STAT);
  312.   res = gc_full_major_exn();
  313.   if (Is_exception_result(res)) goto out;
  314.   res = caml_gc_quick_stat(Val_unit);
  315. out:
  316.   CAML_EV_END(EV_EXPLICIT_GC_STAT);
  317.   return caml_raise_if_exception(res);
  318. }
